Package cs1302.shapes

Class Circle

  • java.lang.Object
    • cs1302.shapes.Shape
      • cs1302.shapes.Ellipse
        • cs1302.shapes.Circle
  • public class Circle
extends Ellipse
    A circle is an Ellipse where both focul points are in the same location. It therefore defines a curve in a plane surrounding a single focul point, such that the distance to the focul point is constant for every point on the curve. The line through the focul point is called the diameter. Half of this length is called the radius, denoting the distance from the focul point to any point on the curve.
